description:
Round 2 gap analysis: Missed because focus was on runtime behavior, not compiler warnings.

At lines 1139-1141:
```c
struct lichen_l2_ctx {
    /* Empty by design - see comment above */
};
```

An empty struct has size 0 in C (unlike C++ where it has size 1). While the comment explains why it's empty, some compilers emit warnings for zero-size structures. GCC -Wpedantic or -Wempty-struct may warn about this.

The code works correctly - NET_DEVICE_INIT just needs a type name, not actual data. But it could cause spurious warnings in strict build configurations.

Fix: Add a dummy uint8_t field if warnings are observed, or suppress the warning for this file.
